  "en:aikido-alternative": { meta: {"title":"Aikido Security alternative: Fleuret AI as the specialist agentic pentest pick (2026)","description":"Aikido Security is the fastest European cybersecurity unicorn with 50,000+ organisations using its all-in-one SAST/DAST/IaC/cloud/AI-pentest suite. Here is the honest comparison vs Fleuret AI for EU buyers choosing between a consolidate-vendors play and a specialist agentic pentest.","date":"2026-05-15","author":"Yanis Grigy, CEO","tags":["Aikido alternative","Comparison","Buyer guide","DORA","NIS2","Sovereignty"],"locale":"en","slug":"aikido-alternative","draft":false,"audience":"direct","faqs":[{"question":"Is Fleuret AI a direct Aikido Security alternative?","answer":"Yes when the buyer wants a pentest specialist. Aikido is an all-in-one AppSec suite (SAST, DAST, IaC, container, secrets, cloud, plus an AI pentest module). Fleuret is a multi-agent agentic pentest specialist with shipped DORA Article 24 + NIS2 Annex I mappings by default. The choice is suite vs specialist."},{"question":"When should I pick Aikido over Fleuret AI?","answer":"Pick Aikido when the buying logic is 'consolidate 9+ AppSec point tools into one platform', when broad coverage and time-to-value matter more than per-module depth, or when the organisation lacks existing SAST / cloud / runtime tooling."},{"question":"When should I pick Fleuret AI over Aikido?","answer":"Pick Fleuret when pentest is a primary buying centre (not a feature in a suite), when SAST / cloud / runtime are already covered by other tools, and when the audit PDF must map to DORA Article 24 or NIS2 Annex I directly without manual reformatting."},{"question":"How do the two vendors compare on EU sovereignty?","answer":"Both are EU-headquartered (Fleuret in France, Aikido in Belgium). Aikido offers EU and US hosting flexibility. Fleuret runs documented open-weight LLMs (gpt-oss-120b, Kimi K2.5, Mistral) exclusively on Scaleway France with no US LLM dependency in the data path."},{"question":"Are Aikido Attack and Fleuret AI directly comparable on pentest module depth?","answer":"Both run autonomous pentest. The benchmark question is validated-finding rate on identical scope. Aikido Attack is one module inside a suite; Fleuret AI is purpose-built end-to-end (recon, plan, exploit, validate, sign). Specialist depth vs suite-module depth is the trade-off."},{"question":"Can a customer run both Aikido and Fleuret?","answer":"Yes. Some buyers use Aikido for SAST + cloud + IaC + secrets and plug Fleuret in for the pentest layer specifically. The vendors are complementary when the suite handles breadth and the specialist handles pentest depth + regulatory deliverables."}],"kind":"blog","readingTimeMinutes":7,"path":"/blog/aikido-alternative","hreflangPath":"/blog/aikido-alternative"}, load: () => import("./blog/en/aikido-alternative.mdx") },
